Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2532471\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2532471\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 13, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104tqc1665702951155.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tqc1665702951155.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tqc1665702951155.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"tqc1665702951155\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Table Management on MySQL\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Tables are created on the fly, or by SQL scripts generated with by the Create Table utility. When you first attempt to access a table, Uniface needs to know if it exists. If the table does not exist, Uniface creates and indexes it, using the information from the application model.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tqc1665702951155__p_d53957e1_d53958e1_d53959e1\">The table is created in the following way:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tqc1665702951155__li_d25070e1_d25071e1_d25072e1\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">create table</code> statement is issued. The primary key constraint is created within table creation.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tqc1665702951155__li_d25073e1_d25074e1_d25075e1\">Indexes are created with the <code class=\"ph codeph\">create index</code> statement.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tqc1665702951155__p_d53960e1_d53961e1_d53962e1\">Overflow tables are created on the fly when needed. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qwi1665702727550.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qwi1665702727550.html\">MySQL Data Packing</a> . An overflow table contains the primary key from the base table, and the overflow information from the field that causes the overflow table. The name for an overflow table consists of the same name as the lowercase entity name with the prefix ‘o’.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"tqc1665702951155__note_w3469ab1b5b7_w3470ab1b5_w3471ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The overflow mechanism is a technical encoding for larger amounts of data, and is not transparent to other applications.</div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tqc1665702951155__section_zkd_2km_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d98410e79\">Segmented Field Support</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tqc1665702951155__p_d53966e1_d53967e1_d53968e1\">The U4.0 MQL connector supports segmented fields. By\n        default, packing codes with the prefix S (SC, SR, SU, SW) are mapped to large object data\n        types. This can be disabled using the connector option <code class=\"ph codeph\">segmented fields:\n          disabled</code>. In this case, Uniface uses the overflow tables mechanism. For more\n        information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pam1665702726925.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pam1665702726925.html\" title=\"Specify whether segmented fields will be stored to large object data types.\">segmented fields</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tqc1665702951155__p_d53969e1_d53970e1_d53971e1\">For the MQL U2.1 and U3.0 connectors, the overflow table\n        mechanism is used to support large data fields.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tqc1665702951155__section_lpf_fkm_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d98410e102\">Limits</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tqc1665702951155__p_d53975e1_d53976e1_d53977e1\">For specific details about the MySQL Server limits for\n        records, indexes, tables, and fields for your chosen storage engine, consult the MySQL\n        documentation.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532471\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532471\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Table Management on MySQL Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 13, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Table Management on MySQL Tables are created on the fly, or by SQL scripts generated with by the Create Table utility. When you first attempt to access a table, Uniface needs to know if it exists. If the table does not exist, Uniface creates and indexes it, using the information from the application model. The table is created in the following way: The create table statement is issued. The primary key constraint is created within table creation. Indexes are created with the create index statement. Overflow tables are created on the fly when needed. For more information, see MySQL Data Packing . An overflow table contains the primary key from the base table, and the overflow information from the field that causes the overflow table. The name for an overflow table consists of the same name as the lowercase entity name with the prefix ‘o’. Note: The overflow mechanism is a technical encoding for larger amounts of data, and is not transparent to other applications. Segmented Field Support The U4.0 MQL connector supports segmented fields. By default, packing codes with the prefix S (SC, SR, SU, SW) are mapped to large object data types. This can be disabled using the connector option segmented fields: disabled . In this case, Uniface uses the overflow tables mechanism. For more information, see segmented fields . For the MQL U2.1 and U3.0 connectors, the overflow table mechanism is used to support large data fields. Limits For specific details about the MySQL Server limits for records, indexes, tables, and fields for your chosen storage engine, consult the MySQL documentation. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}